data.chText: 驾驶（船、汽车等）；掌控方向盘
data.enText: to control the direction in which a boat, car, etc. moves
He steered the boat into the harbour.

data.chText: 他抓住她的胳膊，把她带往门口。
data.enText: He took her arm and steered her towards the door.
to move in a particular direction
The ship steered a course between the islands.
to take control of a situation and influence the way in which it develops

data.chText: 他设法把话题从他离婚一事上引开。
data.enText: He managed to steer the conversation away from his divorce.
She steered the team to victory.

data.chText: 本领就在于避开这两个极端，走中间路线。
data.enText: The skill is in steering a middle course between the two extremes.
a bull (= a male cow) that has been castrated (= had part of its sex organs removed), kept for its meat

ex.enText: He taught me how to drive a tractor/truck.

synonyms.bx: 通常指驾驶小汽车、卡车、公共汽车等机动车辆，但也可指驾船，强调人是驾驶的主体。

ex.chText: 他引导那条船驶过运河。
ex.enText: He piloted the boat through the canal.

synonyms.bx: 指驾驶飞机或宇宙飞船，也可指给船舶领航。

ex.chText: 他认为任何人都能够在没有风浪的水域驾驶这艘船。
ex.enText: He believes that anyone can steer this boat in calm waters.
Stop steering with only one hand!

synonyms.bx: 指驾驶船、车、飞机等，但通常指驾船，强调在行驶方向上的引导。

data.enText: to avoid a person or thing because it may cause problems

example: he got a tip on the stock market
a good lead for a job

tr: be a guiding or motivating force or drive
example: The teacher steered the gifted students towards the more challenging courses

value.def: When you steer a car, boat, or plane, you control it so that it goes in the direction that you want.

example.ex: What is it like to steer a ship this size?...
example.tran: 驾驶这么大的船感觉怎么样？

example.ex: When I was a kid, about six or seven, she would often let me steer the car along our driveway.
example.tran: 在我小时候，大概六七岁时，她经常让我在自家的车道上开车。

value.def: If you steer people towards a particular course of action or attitude, you try to lead them gently in that direction.

example.ex: The new government is seen as one that will steer the country in the right direction...
example.tran: 新政府被认为能将国家引向正确的方向。

example.ex: I think you are perfectly correct in trying to steer your mother towards increased independence.
example.tran: 我认为你试图引导你母亲变得更加独立是完全正确的。

value.tran: 引导，指导(某人采取某种行动或态度)

value.def: If you steer someone in a particular direction, you guide them there.

example.ex: Nick steered them into the nearest seats.
example.tran: 尼克将他们领到最近的座位上。

value.def: If you steer a particular course, you take a particular line of action.

example.ex: Prime Minister Hun Sen has sought to steer a course between the two groups...
example.tran: 洪森首相设法游走于两个集团之间。

example.ex: In nearly all these issues the British steered a middle course.
example.tran: 英国人几乎在所有这些问题上都选择了中间路线。

value.tran: 选择某种做法;采取某种方式

value.def: A steer is a bull that has been castrated.
If you steer clear of someone or something, you deliberately avoid them.

example.ex: I think a lot of people, women in particular, steer clear of these sensitive issues.
example.tran: 我认为很多人，特别是女性，都会回避这些敏感问题。
